column3: This column represents how much volume should be fed over the course of 1 minute, i.e. how much the weight should have dropped over that 1 minute. The volume amount does not increase smoothly between timepoints because I added a compensating amount of volume to minimize the error from dilution. The starting mass will actually be closer to 10000, as we are putting the feed on a stir plate, on the scale. At ~10.15 hours, we switch from continuous to constant feed. This is because that is the threshold at which u = 0.2 =dilution rate. In other words, continue to feed at the same rate past t=10.15, ~6.66ml/min / ~400ml/hr.
True volume fed during timepoint, in litres
